# CI and Deployment Guardrails

## CI baseline

- CI should run at least: typecheck, lint, test, and build.
- Prefer `npm ci` in CI for deterministic installs.
- Cache dependency and build artifacts where safe.

## Data-sensitive checks

- Run data validation and stat generation checks in CI.
- Fail CI when generated outputs are stale versus source data.

## Vercel

- Keep production build command identical to CI build command.
- Keep environment variable names documented in repo (`docs/deployment.md` or equivalent).
- Never commit secrets; use GitHub/Vercel secret stores only.
